The third group contains the largest number of species (Table 
2
) and is mainly characterised by the marked separation of the female and male gonopores. Species of this group show different 
types
of prostatic and sperm ducts junctions, as well as varying sizes and shapes of penis papillae and external vaginas. Species of this group include 

